File:Â Around 2,000 Clover workers are on strike. Google Earth JOHANNESBURG - Refusing to be milked for their work. Around 2,000 Clover workers are on strike. The General Industries Workers Union of SA is demanding a 16 percent wage increase. Clover's offering a 3 percent hike, which has already been rejected. Milk is a staple in many South African households and there's a worry the strike could impact supply.